args: Yo, can we get two teas over here?\nMake mine real bitter, if you would.

Hey, so have you ever bought some chow
to take home for dinner and ended up
eating it as you walked because you just
couldn't wait another second?
That was me. I finally had that relic,\nand I was ITCHING to try it out. So...
Er, I'm afraid we don't need any aid of\nthe military sort, sir. This is a sleepy\nlittle area—we don't even get bandits.
Yeah, but there's gotta be SOMETHING\nthat's bothering you. Think, man!
What about those fiends who live\nin the forest a ways from here?
See! I KNEW there had to be something!\nYou just leave those fiends to me!

Er, all right? Still, it's not like they're
much of a bother—they never leave
the woods, and we've little reason
to go in there after them.

Please, sir, leave the creatures be.
Provoking them can only serve to
stir their ire and cause them to
seek revenge against us.
And what if they come after you first, huh?\nThen it'll be too late for my help!
S-still, I'm just not sure it's worth it...
Look, stop worryin' about it, all right?\nOnce I take care of 'em, there won't\nbe anything left TO take revenge!
...There they are.\nThere's more than I expected.
Use the Jiu Chi Dingba! Quickly!
Oh, I'm on it... And a swing!
Ah! The fiends are powerless before such\nforce of wind!
And one more swing! Go, go!
Hee hee! Incredible! You just turned\nan entire swarm of fiends to ash!
And all I did was swing the thing around!\nYou weren't kiddin' about these relics...
Right then, time to put the fire out.\nDo I swing this thing backward or what?
I thought that organization let you look\nat all their secret relic manuals!
Yeees, but there was nothing in there\nabout the relic DOUSING fires—\nmerely about starting them.
Well, we gotta do SOMETHING!\nIt's getting out of control!
I fear we lack the power.
I can't believe you're givin' up already...\nRrrrr! Fine then! I'll just whip up some\nwind to blow the fire out!
Aw, crap! The wind turned into a tornado!
Which is becoming one with the flames!\nHow simply ASTOUNDING...
First we had a fire, and now we got a\nfire TORNADO? What're we gonna DO?!
Oh dear. It seems our flaming whirlwind\nis moving off in the direction of...

Hmm? Oh, look. It's those travelers who
went to exterminate those forest fiends.
Er, but why are they running at us with
such panicked expressions...?
And why is there a flaming tornado\nright behind 'em?!
How do we run from THAT?!
HmmMMM... Judging by the windspeed\nand the basic geography of this region,\nthe hill behind the village should be safe.
Make for the hill, now!\nI'll carry anyone who can't run!
We led the villagers to safety on the hill,\nwhich gave everyone a perfect view as\nmy damn tornado ravaged their town.
(This is all my fault. If I didn't interfere...)
Enough. Fields and homes can be rebuilt—\nwhat matters is that we have our lives.
Thank you, travelers. Had you not come\nto warn us, I dread to think what would\nhave happened.
Don't thank us. This is all—
No, I insist. You are village heroes!
I ain't no hero. That tornado was—
Has anyone seen my son?!\nI can't find him anywhere!
What!? Could he still be in the village?!
No, you can't go back!\nIt's too dangerous!
Stay here, lady! I've got this!
Dammit all!\nI'm no hero! I'm the world's biggest fool!
Hang on, kiddo! It's gonna be okay!
Hold on and I'll get you back to your mom!\nThe path I took to get here is still...
Damn it all! The fire's movin' so fast\nit swallowed up my path!
Flame on one side, tornado on the other...\nIf I don't do something right now,\nour gooses are cooked...
There's only one person who deserves\nto die today...and it's ME!
Hold tight, kiddo! Don't let go!
This is gonna be hot, but hang in there!\nHere we goooooo!
Y-your feet are gonna catch fire!
That don't matter if I get you back safe!
I won't let myself die until then!\nRAAAAAH!
Look! The traveler found your boy!
There ya go, lady... Your kid's...safe...
